in wrist and finger extension, but triceps strength is preserved. Sensation is intact over the hand.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Peroneal neuropathy","Hereditary neuropathy","Diabetic neuropathy","Ulnar neuropathy","Radial neuropathy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s symptoms are characteristic of a \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E. The radial nerve is responsible for the extension of the wrist and fingers, and compression at the spiral groove can lead to weakness in these muscles while sparing the triceps, as the triceps are innervated by the radial nerve before it reaches the spiral groove.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeroneal neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E presents with foot drop rather than wrist drop, as it affects the muscles responsible for dorsiflexion of the foot.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHereditary neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E often presents with a more gradual onset and may involve multiple nerves, rather than the sudden, isolated wrist drop seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetic neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E usually presents with a distal symmetric polyneuropathy (\u0027glove and stocking\u0027 distribution), often affecting sensation before motor function, and is less likely to cause isolated wrist drop.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUlnar neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E affects the intrinsic muscles of the hand and may cause clawing of the fingers, but it does not cause wrist drop.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Radial neuropathy presents with wrist and finger drop due to weakness of the extensor muscles.","Compression of the radial nerve at the spiral groove spares the triceps muscle.","Sudden onset of wrist and finger drop without pain is characteristic of radial nerve compression."],"references":["Chalk C. Radial neuropathy. Handb Clin Neurol. 2024;201:127-134. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-323-90108-6.00015-6. PMID: 38697735.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Merryman J, Varacallo M. Klumpke Palsy. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30285395"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61378"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17544"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61378","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61378"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T05:15:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T05:15:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10234"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75865"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic